Menu="NetworkServices:50"
Title="Traefik Label Manager"
Icon="globe"
Tag="traefik"
---
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/plugins/traefik.label.manager/styles/traefik-label-manager.css?v=2026.07.21.7">
<section id="traefik-label-manager-settings">
  <div class="tlm-page-header">
    <div>
      <h2>Container labels</h2>
      <p>View active labels and edit the values saved in each Unraid container template.</p>
    </div>
    <button id="tlm-refresh" type="button">Refresh</button>
  </div>
  <section class="tlm-domain-settings">
    <div>
      <label for="tlm-domain-suffix"><strong>Domain suffix</strong></label>
      <span>Used for automatic routes. Enter DNS labels without a wildcard; a leading dot is optional.</span>
    </div>
    <input id="tlm-domain-suffix" type="text" autocomplete="off" spellcheck="false" placeholder="home.arpa">
    <button id="tlm-save-domain" type="button">Save Domain</button>
  </section>
  <p class="tlm-notice"><strong>Enable Route</strong> stages automatic hostname and backend defaults. Additions are limited to labels supported by Traefik's Docker provider; hover or focus the <strong>?</strong> beside a label for details. <strong>Save Template</strong> is non-disruptive. Docker labels change only when the container is recreated; use <strong>Apply &amp; Restart</strong> to run Unraid's container update immediately.</p>
  <div id="tlm-page-message" role="status"></div>
  <div id="tlm-containers" aria-live="polite"><div class="tlm-loading">Loading containers…</div></div>
</section>
<div id="tlm-update-modal" class="tlm-modal" hidden>
  <div class="tlm-modal-card">
    <div class="tlm-modal-header"><strong id="tlm-update-title">Applying container template</strong><button id="tlm-update-close" type="button">Close</button></div>
    <iframe id="tlm-update-frame" title="Unraid container update"></iframe>
  </div>
</div>
<script src="/plugins/traefik.label.manager/javascript/traefik-label-settings.js?v=2026.07.21.7"></script>
